'''Palpatine's apartment''' was a suite of rooms maintained by [[Darth Sidious|Sheev Palpatine]] during his [[time]] as the [[senator]] of [[Naboo]]. It was was located in the upper levels of ''[[500 Republica]]'' in the [[Federal District|Senate District]] of [[Imperial City|Galactic City]] on the [[planet]] [[Coruscant]]. The [[Monarch of Naboo|queen of Naboo]] [[Padmé Amidala]] stayed in the apartment as Palpatine's guest during the [[Invasion of Naboo]].

==Description==
[[File:Coruscant_apartment_view.png|thumb|left|250px|The apartment offered a panoramic view of Galactic City on Coruscant.]]
Within the upper levels of ''[[500 Republica]]''&mdash;the most prestigious and exclusive residential tower located in the [[Federal District|Senate District]] of the [[planet]] [[Coruscant]]&mdash;[[Senator]] [[Darth Sidious|Sheev Palpatine]] of [[Naboo]] kept an apartment<ref name="Ultimate" /> that included a view of [[Imperial City|Galactic City]].<ref name="TPM">{{Film|I}}</ref> The apartment had majestic views but was modest in comparison to other members of the [[Galactic Senate]]. Palpatine had the apartment decorated in hues of red with various unusual art objects and it was wired with discreet security and surveillance equipment.<ref name="Ultimate" />

==History==
===A Senator's abode===
{{Quote|Please, Your Majesty, stay here where it's safe.''"<br />"''It is clear to me now that the Republic no longer functions. I pray you will bring sanity and compassion back to the Senate.|Sheev Palpatine and Padmé Amidala|<ref name="TPM" />}}
[[File:Senator_palpatine.png|thumb|right|250px|Sheev Palpatine resided in an apartment suite in ''500 Republica'' during his tenure as the senator of Naboo.]]
After [[Monarch of Naboo|Queen of Naboo]] [[Padmé Amidala]] and her retinue&mdash;which had been joined by the [[Jedi]] [[Qui-Gon Jinn]] and [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]]&mdash;had arriving on Coruscant following a brief stopover on the planet [[Tatooine]] in the [[Outer Rim Territories]] for repairs, Senator Palpatine brought the [[Queen]] and her retinue to his apartment suite located within ''500 Republica'', while the Jedi made their way to the [[High Council Tower]] to report to the [[Jedi High Council]]. Nonetheless, the young [[Force-sensitive]] [[Anakin Skywalker]], whom Jinn had rescued from slavery on Tatooine on the belief that he was the [[Jedi Order]]'s prophesied [[Chosen One]], and the [[Gungan]] [[Jar Jar Binks]], who had joined the Jedi's journey after saving Jinn's life, also were brought along to the apartment.<ref name="TPM" />

A short time after arriving at the apartment, Skywalker and Binks were waiting outside the apartment's sitting room, with the Gungan sitting in a small chair. [[Captain]] [[Quarsh Panaka]] walked passed them as he entered the sitting room, where Amidala sat on a small couch as two of her handmaidens stood behind her on either side. Panaka stood off to the side as Palpatine paced before the young queen, relating about the corruption within the [[Galactic Senate]] and how there was little chance of the Senate taking action in response to the [[Trade Federation]]'s [[invasion of Naboo]]. Amidala stated that [[Supreme Chancellor]] [[Finis Valorum]] believed there was chance to which Palpatine informed her that the Chancellor held little real power in the Senate. Amidala then asked what their options were.<ref name="TPM" />

[[File:Visitation.png|thumb|left|250px|Queen Padmé Amidala briefly resided in Palpatine's apartment as the senator's guest during the Invasion of Naboo.]]
Moving towards the young queen, Palpatine stated that the election of a new Supreme Chancellor was their best option, suggesting she call for a [[Vote of No Confidence]] in Valorum. Stunned by the senator's words, Amidala countered with how Valorum had been supporting them. Palpatine stepped back and started to pace again as he explained their only other option was to go to the courts and submit their plea. Remaining in her seat, Queen Amidala voiced her frustration, reiterating their people were dying and that they needed a fast solution. Palpatine stood still as he gave his queen an apologetic look before pacing again, informing her that for the moment they would have to accept Federation control of their planet. The senator stopped and looked back to Queen Amidala as she informed him she could not do what he was suggesting. Meanwhile, outside the sitting room, Skywalker pulled Binks out of his chair and led him off.<ref name="TPM" />

===Room fit for a chancellor===
The [[Invasion of Naboo]], which had in secret been masterminded by Palpatine in his alter ego of the [[Dark Lord of the Sith]] [[Darth]] Sidious, culminated in him being elected [[Supreme Chancellor]] of the Republic, replacing Valorum<ref name="TPM" /> and making a major advancement in his [[Grand Plan]] to take total control of [[the galaxy]].<ref name="ROS">{{Film|III}}</ref> Palpatine continued to make use of his apartment during his time as the chancellor and into the [[Clone Wars]],<ref name="Friends and Enemies" /> a [[galaxy]]-wide conflict between the Republic and breakaway [[Confederacy of Independent Systems]] that had, in secret, also been masterminded by Palpatine.<ref name="ROS" /> In [[20 BBY]],<ref name="TCWDate">{{TCWcanondates|416}}</ref> as fears around a [[plot to assassinate Chancellor Palpatine]] began to take root, [[Clone Captain]] [[Rex]]<ref name="Friends and Enemies" />&mdash;an elite and high-ranking [[clone trooper]]<ref name="UltimateNew">''[[Ultimate Star Wars, New Edition]]''</ref> who served under the now-[[Jedi Knight]] Skywalker, who had developed a close bond with Palpatine&mdash;was ordered to personally escort the Chancellor back to his apartment. While Palpatine displayed annoyance at the added security, he allowed the [[captain]] to join him on his journey home from the [[Emperor's office|Chancellor's office]] after speaking to [[Jedi Master]] [[Mace Windu]] about Skywalker's whereabouts.<ref name="Friends and Enemies" />

